<li id="cite_note-Saul_Cornell_AWRM_Bishop-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Saul_Cornell_AWRM_Bishop_31-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFCornell.2C_Saul2006">Cornell, Saul (2006). <i>A WELL-REGULATED MILITIA&#160;– The Founding Fathers and the Origins of Gun Control in America</i>. New York, New York: Oxford University Press. pp.&#160;188. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780195147865" class="internal">ISBN 978-0-19-514786-5</a>.  "”Dillon endorsed Bishop's view that <i>Buzzard's</i> “Arkansas doctrine,” not the libertarian views exhibited in <i>Bliss, captured the dominant strain of American legal thinking on this question.”"</i></cite><i><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+WELL-REGULATED+MILITIA%26nbsp%3B%26ndash%3B++The+Founding+Fathers+and+the+Origins+of+Gun+Control+in+America&amp;rft.aulast=Cornell%2C+Saul&amp;rft.au=Cornell%2C+Saul&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B188&amp;rft.place=New+York%2C+New+York&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-19-514786-5&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Gun_politics_in_the_United_States"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></i></li>
