<li id="cite_note-Guns_used_in_crime-64"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Guns_used_in_crime_64-0" title="">^</a></b> Semi-automatic refers to “an autoloading action that will fire only a single shot for each single function for a trigger” whereas fully automatic refers to the “capability to fire a succession of cartridges so long as the trigger is depressed or until the ammunition supply is exhausted”.<cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFU.S._Department_of_Justice1995">U.S. Department of Justice (July 1995). <a href="http://www.ojp.usdoj.gov/bjs/pub/pdf/guic.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ojp.usdoj.gov/bjs/pub/pdf/guic.pdf" rel="nofollow">"Guns Used in Crime"</a>. U.S. Department of Justice<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.ojp.usdoj.gov/bjs/pub/pdf/guic.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.ojp.usdoj.gov/bjs/pub/pdf/guic.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.ojp.usdoj.gov/bjs/pub/pdf/guic.pdf</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Guns+Used+in+Crime&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=U.S.+Department+of+Justice&amp;rft.au=U.S.+Department+of+Justice&amp;rft.date=July+1995&amp;rft.pub=U.S.+Department+of+Justice&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ojp.usdoj.gov%2Fbjs%2Fpub%2Fpdf%2Fguic.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Gun_politics_in_the_United_States"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
